---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="AI Configuration">
  <h2>AI Configuration</h2>
  <p>
    Rep-li-bot uses OpenAI-compatible APIs for AI-powered code generation.
    Configure your AI provider to enable this feature.
  </p>

  <h3>Settings Panel</h3>
  <p>
    Access AI settings from the Settings menu in the top bar, then select "AI Settings".
  </p>

  <h3>Configuration Options</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Provider Label</strong> - A friendly name for your provider (e.g., "ChatGPT", "Codex")</li>
    <li><strong>Base URL</strong> - The API endpoint URL</li>
    <li><strong>Model</strong> - The model identifier (e.g., <code>gpt-4</code>, <code>gpt-3.5-turbo</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>API Key</strong> - Your API key for authentication</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Common Configurations</h3>

  <h4>OpenAI (ChatGPT)</h4>
  <pre><code>Base URL: https://api.openai.com/v1
Model: gpt-4</code></pre>

  <h4>Azure OpenAI</h4>
  <pre><code>Base URL: https://YOUR_RESOURCE.openai.azure.com/v1
Model: your-deployment-name</code></pre>

  <h4>Self-Hosted / Local</h4>
  <pre><code>Base URL: http://localhost:11434/v1 (Ollama)
Model: codellama</code></pre>

  <h3>Security</h3>
  <p>
    Your API key is stored locally in your workspace and is never exposed
    to the iframe preview harness or transmitted anywhere except to your
    configured AI provider.
  </p>

  <h3>Environment Variables</h3>
  <p>
    For automated builds, you can inject provider defaults using environment variables:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>REPLIBOT_AI_PROVIDER_LABEL</code></li>
    <li><code>REPLIBOT_AI_BASE_URL</code></li>
    <li><code>REPLIBOT_AI_MODEL</code></li>
    <li><code>REPLIBOT_AI_API_KEY</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Troubleshooting</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Invalid API key</strong> - Verify your key is correct and active</li>
    <li><strong>Rate limiting</strong> - Check your API plan limits</li>
    <li><strong>Connection errors</strong> - Verify your internet connection and firewall settings</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
